703795f-a.title: Brooklyn: Conklin Avenue - 93rd Street (East)
703795f-a.text:
Conklin Ave., at the S.W. corner of East 93rd Street, showing the German
Evang. Lutheran Church, which was erected in 1877. It's cornerstone was
laid on June 29, 1877. On November 4th of the same year, the church was
dedicated. The structure cost '5,000. It does not appear in the 1929
realty atlas.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
